---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="HVAC & Home Services — Nate Whiteman"
  description="Custom dashboards, job-costing tools, and dispatch analytics for HVAC companies and home service businesses in East Tennessee."
>

  <div class="back-bar">
    <a href="/services" class="back-link">← All services</a>
  </div>

  <section class="stub-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="stub-eyebrow">East Tennessee · HVAC &amp; Home Services</div>
      <h1 class="stub-title">Built for the businesses that keep things running</h1>
      <p class="stub-lead">
        HVAC companies, plumbers, electricians, and home service contractors deal with
        a specific kind of data chaos — technician schedules, job costs, seasonal swings,
        and equipment histories living in four different places. I build the tools that
        pull it together.
      </p>
      <a href="/services#inquiry" class="btn btn--primary">Talk about your operation →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stub-uses">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2 class="stub-uses-heading">What I build for HVAC &amp; home service companies</h2>
      <ul class="stub-uses-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Technician performance dashboard</strong> — track jobs completed, revenue per tech,
          callback rates, and utilization by week or season.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Job costing tracker</strong> — compare estimated vs. actual labor and materials
          across every job, surface which job types are actually profitable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Seasonal revenue forecast</strong> — model demand curves from prior-year data
          so you can staff and order inventory ahead of peak season.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Dispatch &amp; scheduling visibility</strong> — connect your scheduling tool
          (ServiceTitan, Housecall Pro, spreadsheet) to a single view of what's happening today.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Equipment &amp; maintenance history</strong> — customer-site equipment logs
          with service intervals, warranty tracking, and upsell flags.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stub-cta">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <p class="stub-cta-note">
        Detailed page for HVAC &amp; home services is being built out. In the meantime,
        reach out directly — I work with service businesses regularly and can scope
        a project in one conversation.
      </p>
      <div class="stub-cta-actions">
        <a href="/services#inquiry" class="btn btn--primary">Start a conversation →</a>
        <a href="/services" class="btn btn--ghost">All services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .back-bar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 50;
    background: rgba(10, 12, 15, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    padding: 12px 0;
  }

  .back-bar .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--duration-base);
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .stub-hero {
    padding: clamp(80px, 10vw, 140px) 0 clamp(60px, 8vw, 100px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .stub-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--accent-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .stub-eyebrow::before {
    content: '';
    width: 32px;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), transparent);
  }

  .stub-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 62px);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.0;
    letter-spacing: -2px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .stub-lead {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .stub-uses {
    padding: clamp(60px, 8vw, 100px) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .stub-uses-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .stub-uses-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .stub-uses-list li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border-default);
  }

  .stub-uses-list li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
  }

  .stub-cta {
    padding: clamp(60px, 8vw, 100px) 0;
  }

  .stub-cta-note {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
  }

  .stub-cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .container--narrow {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
